Jan B. Adoration, N.G.? Vienna, etc. Symbolism: dead trees on left against the delicate fresh foliage on right. column4: <content>[recto] Good Shepherd. The dead tree (the right one of the three on the left, cf. Jan B. Adoration, N.G.? Vienna, etc. Symbolism: dead trees on left against the delicate fresh foliage on right. Death & new life!; The Lambs painted thinly over the drawing (esp. the tempera on canvas) completely different from Northwich picture; The 'good' sleeve and the trousers typical P.B.I. Although the inclusion of short parallel lines for shading also in Northwich, the sleeve is not; [verso] like a sack, as it appears in the Northwich picture.</content>
